{"id":"69f387b8-a049-48c3-a0ff-a46f611e2fcb","title":"1557/07/01: To Lionardo di Buonarroti Simoni","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"c6fbcc1e-ae80-428d-8114-4450dd54126e","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, July 1st, 1557.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"18d9f647-0b2b-474c-85f3-644caad29bf0","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":3,"value":"8532f2fa-b614-4eed-9eae-586327f6a15a","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"6aa558b4-eebc-487d-90ed-7b4c30cd1394","type":"block/alignment/right","start":0,"end":25,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"4b2ae18b-166a-453a-ab19-615f7722c793","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"1c109c78-799b-4895-9f0b-d59af5af2ceb","type":"codex/time-reference","start":11,"end":24,"value":"7a8be32b-f32d-4cda-8157-c99efb466b94","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"e6938eed-cd25-4b1f-8380-5ca7e4c10333","type":"style/superscript","start":17,"end":18,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"6aa558b4-eebc-487d-90ed-7b4c30cd1394","type":"block/alignment/right","value":null,"metadata":[]}]},{"id":"bc35cdb1-a89a-45aa-99e3-b092a6b7fb45","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"df876e72-814d-42a5-8e6d-c1f32d9f79e9","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lionardo,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0I would rather die than lose the Duke\u0027s favour. In all my actions I have always endeavoured to be truthful, and if I have delayed my promised coming to Florence it is because I had always understood that this was to be conditional to my having\u00A0first carried the fabric of St. Peter\u0027s to such a\u00A0stage that the general lines of the composition could\u00A0neither be altered nor ruined, and to prevent the return of the thieves who used to wait, and are still waiting,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"81012151-8874-4603-97c0-f1bb995cf58e","t